This game sure is interesting although to start of i have a few things that really make a reason for such a bad review First of all the graphics are really... disgusting. The game looks like it was made with clay-mation. So really, for people judgy (like me) about gaming graphics i do not recommend purchasing. And second: The trailer you see really makes the game look great. Although the events that you see in the video are rare to come upon, especially the great scoping, aiming, and trick-shots. If anything that looks as if the trailer creator turned on their own personal auto-aim. So don't go getting "too" excited over the trailer. Third: When in gameplay, if you die, you wont be able to respawn until all other players of your team or the other team are dead. So, you could be sitting there for up to 10 minutes watching a bad quality cam of some one else playing. Fourth: The game looks like there wasn't that much effort put into it, like it's home made. when spectating, when zooming out.. the exterior goes completely black, as if all the map is is just a boxed maze. In addition: NO SPRINT!!! So for anyone looking for a good first-person shooter, I surely do not recommend this game.
