Counter Strike 1.6  What else their is to say?
This is Counter-Strike 1.6, the latest version of the original Counter-Strike. The graphics are far inferior to the source version but the gameplay is considered better by most Counter-Strike veterans. This has some maps not found in the source verison and has the riot shield which is not in the source version either. The riot shield allows you to avoid bullets but you cannot have a primary weapon if you have it equiped so you can only use your sidearm. This version also features a gamemode not available in the source version. The gamemode is where you must protect a player controlling a VIP while they make their way to the rescue vehicle. If you want to see how different this is from the source version then go right ahead, it's only $5.00 on steam so you have nothing to lose.
Best FPS of all time
- One of the best games FPS games ever made, Counter-Strike 1.6 left it's mark on the FPS genera. The Community. - The once prospering community has now reduced the number of adepts, simply because the time for Counter-Strike (1.0-1.6) has passed by a little bit and more and more of the once players of Counter-Strike are attracted now to these new big FPS's, and they are right to do that because we need to move and and progress. The Graphics. - Not so astonishing if you put it against the today graphics, we must remember that, it is an old game, the graphics we look at today for this game were some hits back in 2000 and personally I still enjoy the graphics a little, because they are bringing that simplicity, not an eye heavy graphics style. The Sounds. - Well, for me, I still love the sounds in this game, the guns sound like proper powerfull weapons, when you press the button to fire you really feel like you are engaging somebody and you really feel like you are wielding a firearm that could take someones life, not like some of today's FPS's where guns sound more like the pops of the popcorn put in your microwave. So here Counter-Strike still takes the point from some of the new FPS's. - Even with the fact that's Counter-Strike's 1.6 time passed by a little bit, i still recommend it and me too, i still come back to it from time to time to enjoy this nice, simple and clean graphics style, the still impressive gun sounds and sometimes just to see where have we started from and where have we come with the FPS genera. Note. This is a personal opinnion, you may agree or disagree with it, but on whatever side you are, you can leave a nice criticising comment instead of some hateful messages. Thank you.
